            <title>[PIG-2782] Specifying sorting field(s) at nightly.conf</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2782</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After running the Checkin tests, it fails because one of the parameters passed to the sort is incorrect (instead of +1 -2, on POSIX is -k2,2). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to this &lt;a href=&quot;http://ss64.com/bash/sort.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://ss64.com/bash/sort.html&lt;/a&gt;, it was on an old notation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac OS X Lion 10.7.3&lt;br/&gt;
Hadoop 1.0.1-SNAPSHOT&lt;br/&gt;
Apache Pig version 0.11.0-SNAPSHOT (r1355798)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
