                            <comment id="13405129" author="jay23jack" created="Mon, 2 Jul 2012 16:55:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&#65291;1. I also had the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13406284" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 4 Jul 2012 05:34:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is the patch that replaces obsolete sort options with posix options in e2e tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modified tests are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Checkin, Foreach, Order, Types, Limit, Split, MissingColumns, Jython_Checkin, and BigData&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I verified that all tests pass in local mode.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13409814" author="daijy" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 20:28:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Cheolsoo!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495766" author="esoren" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 23:55:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There were still problems with the patch here. E.g. the pig script sorts on column one and two, but the verification only checks that output is sorted on column one.&lt;br/&gt;
